headline.main: R.A.F.'S DAY BOMBERS OUT; Targets in France, Low Countries Hit -- London Has an Alarm

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Tuesday, June 1 (AP) -- British medium bombers and escorting Spitfires made two long sweeps over Northern France and the Low Countries yesterday. The four-motored heavyweights of the R.A.F. remained in their hangars Sunday night after their busiest week of the war last week.
abstract: RAF raids northern France and Low Countries
